OL,3,CJersey's migrant workers are at risk
OL,4,Cof being 'kicked into servitude'
OL,6,F"They believe they have invested
OL,7,Ffinancially in the worker, so
OL,8,Ftherefore they have the right to
OL,9,Fretain that worker and maybe control
OL,10,Fother areas of their lives."
OL,12,FDeputy Poree says the States has "a
OL,13,Flong way to go" to tighten up the work
OL,14,Fpermit policy, to better protect
OL,15,Fworkers from abuse.
